result.execSummary:
The defendant Isis A. Blackwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 12:15 PM: Defendant Isis A. Blackwell in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def advised of right to counsel.  Def waives counsel today and wishes to resolve the matter today without counsel.  Argument as to SEH by DA.  No statement offered by Def.  The Court:  Will accept sentencing recommendation and imposes Court Costs Only - 60 DTP or PP.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  Right to expunge DNA thru DOJ explained to Def.  Appeal Rights Given.
Sentencing hearing on July 11, 2017 at 11:45 am.

8:12 am cases called-15CM499 & 16CM108. Defendant Isis A Blackwell in court with attorney Michael D. Petersen.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court goes over hearing on calendar for today. Agreement reached.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant. Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to 16CM108. Court accepts plea and stays JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 15CM499. Argument by State regarding terms of PPDA. Argument by Attorney Petersen regarding terms of PPDA. Statement by defendant. Court accepts terms and conditions of Deferred Sentencing Agreement-conditions of bond in 16CM108. Matter stayed for 12 months. Court admonishes the defendant regarding conditions of bond.
Status conference on July 6, 2016 at 08:00 am.

Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department. Court does not prevent defendant from conducting door to door sales; however, the court prohibits the defendant from having any other person with her while conducting door to door sales. Court requires before engaging in any door to door activity-defendant is to contact the Sheriff's Department of the municipality where she will be going from door to door with her name, date of birth, vehicle license plate number, and product she is attempting to sell so the Sheriff's Department is aware of her activity.

2:50 pm cases called. Defendant Isis A. Blackwell in court with attorney Michael D. Petersen.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    NGP entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for July 6, 2016 at 08:00 am.
Initial appearance on April 5, 2016 at 02:45 pm.
